    text: "The Boxers were a secret society in China around the year 1900. Their Chinese name meant 'Righteous and Harmonious Fists.' Western people called them 'Boxers' because they practiced martial arts and physical exercises. The members of this group were very angry about foreign people in China. They hated the Christian missionaries and European traders who were changing their culture. The Boxers believed that their special training and rituals made them immune to bullets and swords. They thought modern weapons could do them no harm. This belief gave them the courage to fight against powerful armies. In 1900, they started a violent uprising called the Boxer Rebellion. They attacked foreign embassies in Beijing and killed many people. The Empress of China supported them for a short time. However, a large army from eight different countries invaded China to stop them. The Boxers were defeated because their magic protection offered no real defense. The rebellion ended in 1901, and China was forced to pay a huge amount of money to the foreign powers.",
