    text: "The Carbonari were a secret network of revolutionaries in Italy in the 1800s. Their name means 'Charcoal Burners.' They were called this because they met in secret places like forests where people made charcoal. They were no criminals like the Mafia. They were political fighters. They wanted Italy to be a free and united country with a constitution. At that time, Italy was divided and ruled by foreign kings. The Carbonari wanted to overthrow these kings. They had secret handshakes and complex rituals to protect their members. Many important Italian patriots were members. They organized revolts and protests against the government. Although they failed many times and were often arrested or executed, their ideas survived. They helped prepare the people for the eventual unification of Italy. They are remembered as brave men who fought for freedom and democracy in secret. Their work laid the foundation for modern Italy.",
